race.comment: PURR SEFANEE (4) is a leader who was plainer at Launceston last time off a near miss there prior when seeking the hat-trick. Draws low today and Darmanin replaces the 2kg apprentice. She can bounce back. NAVARRE RIVER (1) deserved the Launceston win as favourite racing forward. Runs the mile strongly and is a decent chance to go back-to-back. MILES 'N' MILES (3) hits this at peak off a near miss at Launceston in a CL4. Caries more weight but he's up to this. AL MAXIMUS (2) gets in well with the 3kg claim and will be better over a mile. Is still well shy of his best and deserves consideration as well.
